# Alternative Gemini Extension Test

This file uses the .gemini extension instead of .gmi to test that both extensions are properly recognized and served with the correct MIME type.

## Purpose

Some Gemini servers and clients recognize both:
* .gmi (more common)
* .gemini (alternative)

Both should be served as text/gemini content type.

## Sample Content

=> /test.gmi Compare with .gmi version
=> /index.gmi Return to homepage

```code
function testGeminiExtension() {
    console.log("Both .gmi and .gemini should work!");
}
```

This file helps verify that the server correctly handles multiple Gemini file extensions.